.TH hsf 1 "2026-04-26" "1.0.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
     hsf \- fast and secure hosts file manager

.SH SYNOPSIS
     \fBhsf\fR [\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIARGUMENTS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
     \fBhsf\fR is a system utility for managing the \fI/etc/hosts\fR file. It 
     provides atomic writes, backup management, and a preset system with 
     automatic privilege dropping for secure network operations. Written in Rust.

.SH COMMANDS
     \fBhelp\fR
             Print help information.

     \fBversion\fR
             Print the version of the utility.

     \fBclear\fR
             Clear all entries from the hosts file.

     \fBbase\fR
             Reset the hosts file to the base configuration.

     \fBbackup\fR <\fInew|from|del|list\fR> [\fIarg\fR]
             Manage host file backups:
             \fBnew\fR <\fIname\fR>    Make a new backup.
             \fBfrom\fR <\fIname\fR>   Load a target backup.
             \fBdel\fR <\fIname\fR>    Delete a specific backup.
             \fBlist\fR [\fIsearch\fR]  Print list of backups.
             \fBinfo\fR <\fIname\fR>    Print information about a backup.

     \fBinfo\fR
             Print short info and statistics about the current hosts file.

     \fBcheck\fR <\fIdomain\fR>
             Check where the specified domain points to.

     \fBadd\fR <\fIip\fR> <\fIdomain\fR>
             Add a new IP and domain to the hosts file.

     \fBremove\fR <\fIdomain\fR>
             Remove a domain from the hosts file.

     \fBpreset\fR <\fIload|list\fR> [\fIarg\fR]
             Manage presets:
             \fBload\fR <\fIname\fR>   Load a target preset.
             \fBlist\fR [\fIsearch\fR] Print list of presets.
             <\fIname\fR>        Quickly load a target preset.

.SH SECURITY
     When processing remote presets, \fBhsf\fR drops ROOT privileges before 
     connecting to the network to ensure system integrity.

.SH HISTORY
     Created in 2026 as a high-performance Rust alternative for comfort and security by Vinkoplay.

.SH SEE ALSO
     \fBhosts\fR(5)